Sentencas: Nano-structured Pd-infiltrated YSZ cathodes (Pd + YSZ) are prepared by impregnation method and their electrocatalytic activity and reduction-oxidation behavior are investigated.
Titulo: Redox behavior of supported Pd particles and its effect on oxygen reduction reaction in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is observed that nanosized PdO particles are uniformly distributed on the surface of the YSZ scaffold and decomposed at a temperature below 800 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Redox behavior of supported Pd particles and its effect on oxygen reduction reaction in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Coexistence of Pd and PdO in the Pd + YSZ cathode is detected at temperatures between 650 and 750 degrees C.
Titulo: Redox behavior of supported Pd particles and its effect on oxygen reduction reaction in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance R-E of the Pd + YSZ cathode decreases continuously as oxygen partial pressure increases from 0.001 to 1 atm at 600 and 850 degrees C, whereas it reaches a minimum in the vicinity of 0.03 atm of oxygen partial pressure at 750 degrees C.
Titulo: Redox behavior of supported Pd particles and its effect on oxygen reduction reaction in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In air with an oxygen partial pressure of 0.21 atm, the Pd + YSZ shows the lowest activation energy for the oxygen reduction reaction in the temperature range of 650 and 750 degrees C. (c) 2010
Titulo: Redox behavior of supported Pd particles and its effect on oxygen reduction reaction in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
